{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.2 Batch Auction Priority Bids\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Mechanism}: During the reveal phase of each 10-second batch auction, traders can submit optional priority bids. Higher bids increase the probability of earlier execution within the batch.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Key property}: {\b Priority bids do not affect the clearing price.} All trades in a batch settle at the same uniform price regardless of priority. This means paying for urgency doesn\u8217't extract value from other traders \u8212- it\u8217's a pure fee for service.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Distribution}: 100% to governance stakers and protocol treasury (LPs are already compensated via swap fees).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Why it\u8217's not rent-seeking}: The service is speed, not information advantage. A priority bidder gets faster settlement but the same price as everyone else. No one is harmed by someone else\u8217's priority bid.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.3 Insurance Pool Premiums\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Mechanism}: Users can opt into impermanent loss protection and liquidation insurance via {\f1 ILProtectionVault.sol} and {\f1 VibeInsurance.sol}. Premiums are calculated based on pool volatility and position size.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Rate}: Dynamic, typically 0.1-0.5% of protected position per epoch.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Distribution}: - Insurance pool reserve: 80% (funds payouts) - Insurance pool LPs: 20% (yield for providing insurance capital)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Why it\u8217's not rent-seeking}: Insurance is a voluntary service. Users who don\u8217't want protection pay nothing. Premiums are actuarially determined, not set by governance vote. The pool is fully on-chain and auditable.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.4 Yield Tokenization Fees\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Mechanism}: When users mint Contribution Yield Tokens (CYTs) representing their accumulated protocol contributions, a small fee is collected by {\f1 ShapleyDistributor.sol}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Rate}: 0.5% of tokenized yield value.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Distribution}: 100% to protocol treasury for operational expenses and contributor rewards.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Why it\u8217's not rent-seeking}: CYT minting is a service (converting illiquid contribution history into tradeable tokens). The fee covers the gas and computational cost of Shapley calculation and on-chain verification.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.5 Governance Proposal Deposits\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Mechanism}: Submitting a governance proposal requires a deposit (denominated in protocol tokens). The deposit is returned if the proposal passes or is rejected in good faith. It is {\b slashed} if the proposal is determined to be malicious by the {\f1 DecentralizedTribunal.sol}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Typical deposit}: 1,000-10,000 tokens (scales with proposal impact).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Slashing conditions}: - Proposal contains executable code that drains treasury - Proposal is a duplicate spam submission - Proposal violates hardcoded protocol invariants\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Distribution of slashed deposits}: 50% to tribunal participants (who did the adjudication work), 50% to protocol treasury.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Why it\u8217's not rent-seeking}: The deposit is a Sybil-resistance mechanism, not a fee. Good-faith proposals are fully refunded. Only malicious proposals lose deposits, creating a direct cost for attacking governance.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.6 AI Agent Services (x402 Micropayments)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Mechanism}: JARVIS offers premium analysis services \u8212- portfolio risk assessment, MEV detection alerts, gas optimization recommendations \u8212- via HTTP 402 micropayments using the x402 protocol.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Pricing}: Per-query, denominated in stablecoins or protocol tokens. Typical: $0.01-$0.10 per analysis.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Distribution}: - JARVIS operational costs (LLM inference via Wardenclyffe): 60% - Protocol treasury: 20% - Shapley pool (JARVIS is a contributor): 20%\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Why it\u8217's not rent-seeking}: The service requires active compute (LLM inference costs real money). Users pay per-query for analysis they couldn\u8217't get elsewhere. Pricing is transparent and competitive with centralized alternatives.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 3. Shapley Distribution\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 3.1 What It Is\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Shapley value, from cooperative game theory, assigns each participant a reward proportional to their {\b marginal contribution} \u8212- the difference between the outcome with them and without them.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 For a coalition game with players N and value function v:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 phi_i(v) = SUM over S subset of N\\\{i\}: [|S|!(|N|-|S|-1)!/|N|!] * [v(S union \{i\}) - v(S)]\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 3.2 Why It Matters\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Shapley distribution is the {\b only} distribution method that satisfies all four fairness axioms simultaneously:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Efficiency}: All value is distributed (no residual for protocol insiders)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Symmetry}: Equal contributors get equal rewards\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Null player}: Non-contributors get nothing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab {\b Additivity}: Combined game rewards equal sum of individual game rewards\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 No governance vote can override these mathematical properties. The fairness is proven, not promised.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 3.3 Implementation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 ShapleyDistributor.sol} calculates contributions per epoch: - LP contribution: marginal impact on pool depth and trade execution quality - Staker contribution: security weight and governance participation - Builder contribution: code commits, bug reports, integration work (via {\f1 GitHubContributionTracker.sol}) - JARVIS contribution: community management, code generation, analysis services\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All contributions are on-chain verifiable. Distribution happens automatically at epoch boundaries.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
