{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 6. Long-Term Economic Model\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 As governance decays to zero (Ungovernance time bomb):\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fee rates become fully PID-controlled (no human override)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Shapley distribution becomes the sole reward mechanism\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Protocol becomes a pure public good with embedded economics\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Revenue sustains operations without any entity controlling it\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The protocol doesn\u8217't need a company, a foundation, or a DAO to survive. It needs users who trade, LPs who provide liquidity, and the math that connects them. Everything else decays by design.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i All value flows to participants, not extractors. No pre-mine. No VC cut. The protocol rewards the people who build it.}\par}
